Sentencas: This paper reports a new 3D isothermal, steady state electrochemical modeling study for tubular solid oxide fuel cells where the testing setup is studied in order to improve fuel distribution and geometry.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets

Sentencas: For the model validation, an experimental voltage-current density curve measured in house was used.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets

Sentencas: This study focuses on the cell testing setup and is used to optimize the testing geometry for improved testing conditions.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets

Sentencas: The mathematical model consists of coupling fluid dynamics, electrical conduction, and diffusion physics.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets

Sentencas: The model indicates that flow mal-distribution may be of concern and may affect cell performance.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets

Sentencas: In addition, concentrations of current densities throughout the solid oxide fuel cell may cause some hot spots.
Titulo: Modeling Studies of Tubular SOFCs for Transportation Markets
